song_name: Dont Stop To Watch The Wheels

version_description: This is how I play a simplified version of one of my favorite Doobie tunes. The strum is feel based. I like to play alternating bass notes for the chorus. C-5th string G-6th string and E-4th string B-fifth string respectively. Between the D and B7 chords during the pre-chorus play the Db and C notes on the 5th string. Takes a few listens to nail the interaction between that D chord and those notes.
None of the other chord versions have quite the right chords.
I've viewed and played all of the other versions and none of them have the correct sus4 chord that i have included

version_description: Mccdonald sings a very fluid melody in the verses, so it's easier to learn the groove than to follow the lyrics. Once you get the 3 parts down, it's a great song to jam with.
